00:13:15,730 --> 00:13:17,399
- That was a big blow.
- They're warning me.

307
00:13:17,399 --> 00:13:18,500
So,

308
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:20,470
you're going to get back
with her, right?

309
00:13:22,669 --> 00:13:23,740
I don't know.

310
00:13:23,740 --> 00:13:26,070
I can see from the clip...

311
00:13:26,269 --> 00:13:30,039
that they have so much love...

312
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:33,149
for their moms and dads
in the drama.

313
00:13:33,149 --> 00:13:37,019
You have a huge fandom.

314
00:13:37,179 --> 00:13:39,320
Let's check out the clips...

315
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,289
that The Penthouse kids have
picked out.

316
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:46,659
(They also gathered again.)

317
00:13:47,090 --> 00:13:50,600
(An adorable and hilarious talk)

318
00:13:50,929 --> 00:13:54,730
(The best scenes,
chosen by The Penthouse kids)

319
00:13:54,970 --> 00:13:57,500
When I got the script
for the first episode,

320
00:13:57,899 --> 00:14:01,340
the first thing I read was,
"A girl is dead on the ground."

321
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:04,740
Right. Ro Na.

322
00:14:04,740 --> 00:14:06,779
(A long-haired girl is dead
on the ground!)

323
00:14:06,809 --> 00:14:08,809
They said a girl was lying, dead.

324
00:14:08,809 --> 00:14:10,549
I wondered who it would be.

325
00:14:10,549 --> 00:14:11,879
Who would it be?

326
00:14:11,879 --> 00:14:13,850
I never imagined it would be me.

327
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:16,590
(You're wrong, Bae Ro Na.)

328
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:18,659
Later on, when I read the script,

329
00:14:18,759 --> 00:14:20,629
it said that Ro Na was dead.

330
00:14:21,559 --> 00:14:24,100
"'Ro Na's dead.'
What, Ro Na's dead?"

331
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:25,360
"Eun Byeol killed her?"

332
00:14:29,799 --> 00:14:30,840
I was so surprised.

333
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,139
"Then what happens to me?"

334
00:14:32,809 --> 00:14:35,309
- My only connection...
- They all worry about their share.

335
00:14:35,309 --> 00:14:38,110
- Yes. Ro Na is all he has.
- She's my only plot line...

336
00:14:38,110 --> 00:14:40,049
and she dies?

337
00:14:40,309 --> 00:14:42,509
- I did worry about my share.
- See?

338
00:14:42,950 --> 00:14:45,990
I was very shocked and very upset.

339
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:48,120
(It's okay, Ro Na.)

340
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:50,590
But I had this slight...

341
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:53,629
This strong feeling that
she'd come back.

342
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:56,299
And when the script confirmed it,
I thought, "Okay, great."

343
00:14:57,059 --> 00:14:59,529
Yoon Hee says to Ro Na,

344
00:14:59,529 --> 00:15:00,669
"Ro Na, get up."

345
00:15:00,669 --> 00:15:03,740
"Mom's so scared."
There's that line in a scene.

346
00:15:04,399 --> 00:15:05,399
Ro Na.

347
00:15:06,070 --> 00:15:08,009
Ro Na. Open your eyes.

348
00:15:08,009 --> 00:15:09,779
(Emotional)

349
00:15:09,779 --> 00:15:13,250
Mom's scared. Open your eyes, Ro Na!

350
00:15:13,350 --> 00:15:15,750
I was supposed to be dead then.

351
00:15:15,750 --> 00:15:18,179
Eugene acted out her part
so emotionally.

352
00:15:18,179 --> 00:15:20,220
She was like a real mom.

353
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:23,360
- It was a really cold day.
- I was dead and a tear fell.

354
00:15:23,559 --> 00:15:24,960
I remember that.

355
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,029
(Ro Na's most shocking
and emotional scene)

356
00:15:26,259 --> 00:15:27,830
My dad.

357
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:31,200
Mr. Bong really helped me a lot
with my acting.

358
00:15:31,929 --> 00:15:35,100
In the last episode,

359
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,570
he objects to the sentencing,

360
00:15:37,570 --> 00:15:41,169
and he jumps up and...
Is it called the hammer?

361
00:15:41,169 --> 00:15:43,409
He grabs that and climbs up...

362
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:45,879
- and jumps.
- That was hilarious.

363
00:15:46,549 --> 00:15:47,980
- Joo Dan Tae!
- That was funny.

364
00:15:48,450 --> 00:15:50,120
- I missed it.
- A flying squirrel.

365
00:15:50,250 --> 00:15:54,049
(Kyu Jin the flying squirrel
stood out in this scene.)

366
00:15:54,289 --> 00:15:55,720
Do you know who I am?

367
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:57,860
I couldn't stop laughing
when he shot that scene.

368
00:15:57,860 --> 00:15:59,220
What would you have done without me?

369
00:15:59,220 --> 00:16:00,759
I will show you!

370
00:16:00,759 --> 00:16:03,100
Kyu Jin even shot some footage
on his own.

371
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:07,169
- That clip is worth keeping.
- If there were a Korean Joker,

372
00:16:07,570 --> 00:16:10,870
wouldn't that be Bong Tae Gyu?
That's what I think.

373
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:11,899
What a compliment.

374
00:16:11,899 --> 00:16:15,169
I believed my mom was dead,

375
00:16:15,169 --> 00:16:16,809
and I get to see her again.

376
00:16:17,080 --> 00:16:22,009
(He's reunited with Ro Na and
Su Ryeon whom he thought were dead.)

377
00:16:22,610 --> 00:16:23,980
(Seok Hoon...)

378
00:16:25,549 --> 00:16:26,620
(Mom?)

379
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:28,590
It's so sad
if you just see the highlights.

380
00:16:29,460 --> 00:16:31,289
I almost cried here.

381
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,230
My gosh.

382
00:16:39,259 --> 00:16:41,700
(Mom.)

383
00:16:43,070 --> 00:16:45,139
(I missed you, Seok Hoon.)

384
00:16:45,870 --> 00:16:46,940
Mom.

385
00:16:46,940 --> 00:16:49,509
(I missed you so much.)

386
00:16:49,679 --> 00:16:51,909
From Seok Hoon's standpoint,

387
00:16:51,909 --> 00:16:54,779
people he thought were dead
suddenly reappeared.

388
00:16:54,779 --> 00:16:56,419
So I wasn't sure...

389
00:16:56,419 --> 00:16:58,279
- how to portray my feelings.
- That's true.

390
00:16:58,279 --> 00:16:59,320
"Am I dead?"

391
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:03,190
- I thought I'd be really surprised.
- "Am I dead?"

392
00:17:03,289 --> 00:17:05,259
"I go up to Seo Jin..."

393
00:17:05,519 --> 00:17:07,389
"and do that?"

394
00:17:07,389 --> 00:17:08,830
The last scene of episode four.

395
00:17:08,830 --> 00:17:10,299
I can't...

396
00:17:10,299 --> 00:17:11,960
This was a famous scene.

397
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:16,569
(Seok Kyung blackmails Seo Jin.)

398
00:17:16,569 --> 00:17:18,200
That's why I'm being shameless
and asking you for this favor.

399
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,240
- That scene alone.
- Her Eun Byeol impression's funny.

400
00:17:20,569 --> 00:17:23,240
I thought, "How am I to do this?"

401
00:17:24,140 --> 00:17:28,180
(She pulled it off with
lots of thought and hard work.)

402
00:17:28,849 --> 00:17:31,119
(Look at her act...)

403
00:17:31,119 --> 00:17:32,920
Why did you just run away?

404
00:17:35,589 --> 00:17:36,960
Instead of saving your dad?

405
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,960
(That's a perfect high act!)

406
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:42,960
I was so surprised that scene
was the episode's finale.

407
00:17:43,230 --> 00:17:45,059
Shall we restart our discussion?

408
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:52,369
I imitated Eun Byeol.

409
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,769
She did so well.

410
00:17:54,769 --> 00:17:56,880
- Right? I was surprised.
- The hair thing.

411
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:58,839
(Her Eun Byeol impression
was talk of the town.)

412
00:17:59,039 --> 00:18:00,509
My dad asked you.

413
00:18:00,509 --> 00:18:03,220
That was so funny,
I kept rewatching that part.

414
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:04,220
No!

415
00:18:04,579 --> 00:18:06,450
- It was funny.
- It was.

416
00:18:06,450 --> 00:18:07,519
(Let's watch it.)

417
00:18:07,519 --> 00:18:08,650
No, no.

418
00:18:09,460 --> 00:18:10,589
- No, no.
- Please.

419
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:12,119
Do it just once.

420
00:18:12,519 --> 00:18:13,789
(Shudder of embarrassment)

421
00:18:13,789 --> 00:18:16,230
- She's so embarrassed.
- Let's watch.

422
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:19,299
(Channeling Ha Eun Byeol)

423
00:18:19,930 --> 00:18:21,700
(Ha Eun Byeol carbon copy)

424
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:24,269
Don't make jokes.

425
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,769
My dad asked you.

426
00:18:26,269 --> 00:18:28,109
Just let me compete.

427
00:18:28,109 --> 00:18:29,440
You're the director...

428
00:18:29,779 --> 00:18:32,339
- She did pretty good.
- That was good.

429
00:18:32,339 --> 00:18:33,950
She nailed the details.

430
00:18:34,579 --> 00:18:35,579
Eun Byeol's so sweet.

431
00:18:35,579 --> 00:18:38,049
You're not teasing me,
are you? I'm sorry.

432
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:40,519
The scene that got me emotional...

433
00:18:40,519 --> 00:18:42,250
was where I confess my baldness.

434
00:18:42,250 --> 00:18:43,690
That was so sad.

435
00:18:44,059 --> 00:18:48,789
(Jenny was bullied so much,
the stress caused hair loss.)

436
00:18:53,369 --> 00:18:55,900
- What... What happened?
- This was so sad.

437
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,000
When did this happen?

438
00:18:58,269 --> 00:19:01,269
Jenny had been through a lot...

439
00:19:01,910 --> 00:19:03,009
in season two.

440
00:19:03,009 --> 00:19:04,980
(She was bullied
throughout the season.)

441
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:06,849
She'd wanted to tell her mom,

442
00:19:06,849 --> 00:19:09,980
but she held back
and then it all came out at once.

443
00:19:10,380 --> 00:19:12,519
Ms. Shin said, "Who did this?"

444
00:19:12,519 --> 00:19:15,490
I crumbled when she said that.

445
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:16,589
Who was it?

446
00:19:20,559 --> 00:19:22,829
Who did this to my daughter?

447
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:24,460
Tell me now!

448
00:19:24,900 --> 00:19:26,769
That was so moving.

449
00:19:26,769 --> 00:19:29,500
I watched the episode as a viewer,

450
00:19:29,500 --> 00:19:31,970
and tears kept welling up.

451
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:36,240
Jenny's acting
alongside Ms. Shin's...

452
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:38,779
I felt the maternal love
and connection,

453
00:19:38,779 --> 00:19:41,680
and I also felt
just how hard it must've been...

454
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:44,579
for Jenny and I felt bad for her.

455
00:19:44,579 --> 00:19:46,519
Min Hyuk doesn't think or care,

456
00:19:46,519 --> 00:19:48,890
and he just enjoyed what happened.

457
00:19:49,119 --> 00:19:51,920
I think he's
the worst of all the bullies.

458
00:19:52,059 --> 00:19:54,759
I'm so stressed out
because of my character.

459
00:19:54,759 --> 00:19:55,789
(Stressful headache)

460
00:19:55,789 --> 00:19:57,829
On my personal social media account,

461
00:19:57,829 --> 00:20:00,299
I apologized to
all the Min Hyuks nationwide.

462
00:20:00,299 --> 00:20:03,569
Whenever the drama airs,
all the Min Hyuks get chewed out,

463
00:20:03,569 --> 00:20:04,970
and I felt terrible.

464
00:20:04,970 --> 00:20:06,940
In the bathtub in our home,

465
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:10,339
- I help my mom bathe.
- That scene...

466
00:20:11,140 --> 00:20:13,609
(Jenny found out
what her mom does for a living.)

467
00:20:13,609 --> 00:20:15,809
- Keep still.
- That scene was really...

468
00:20:15,809 --> 00:20:19,079
I'm so grateful towards Ms. Shin.

469
00:20:19,079 --> 00:20:22,920
That day, I had a lot of trouble
getting into the right mindset.

470
00:20:23,059 --> 00:20:26,589
I heard Ms. Shin's voice
where she's emotional and choked up,

471
00:20:26,589 --> 00:20:29,460
and I could feel her trembling
through her back.

472
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:31,960
That suddenly got me emotional.

473
00:20:32,559 --> 00:20:35,329
Even after we'd finished the scene,

474
00:20:35,900 --> 00:20:38,900
even after we were done,
we both kept crying.

475
00:20:38,900 --> 00:20:40,509
Even after the scene.

476
00:20:40,509 --> 00:20:43,480
(It made us think when
we last saw our parents' backs.)

477
00:20:44,609 --> 00:20:47,680
(Which scene
do you remember the most?)

478
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:52,079
(Every scene in
The Penthouse 2 was special.)

479
00:20:52,079 --> 00:20:54,119
That was lovely.

480
00:20:54,119 --> 00:20:56,690
We were watching the clips
and Eugene...

481
00:20:56,690 --> 00:20:57,960
- She cried.
- Yes.

482
00:20:57,960 --> 00:20:59,490
- That's right.
- Ro Na's death.

483
00:20:59,490 --> 00:21:01,359
We were talking about
your crying scene...

484
00:21:01,359 --> 00:21:04,630
- and you cried again.
- I worried when I got the script.

485
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:07,500
"I won't be able to stop crying."

486
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,599
That's what I thought.

487
00:21:08,599 --> 00:21:11,500
Because I have a daughter
in real life,

488
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:13,369
- My gosh.
- It felt...

489
00:21:13,369 --> 00:21:15,109
- Oh, no.
- Yes, right.

490
00:21:15,109 --> 00:21:17,779
To be honest, in my acting career,

491
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:19,539
I really never wanted to...

492
00:21:19,539 --> 00:21:21,980
play a role in which my child dies.

493
00:21:21,980 --> 00:21:24,819
No one knew that Ro Na would die.

494
00:21:24,819 --> 00:21:27,349
So when I got the script...

495
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:30,890
"I really have to do this."

496
00:21:31,019 --> 00:21:34,089
It's really an emotion
you don't want to experience.

497
00:21:34,089 --> 00:21:35,730
Talking about it set her off again.

498
00:21:35,730 --> 00:21:37,000
(She got emotional again.)

499
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:39,430
(They feel how she felt
during the shoot.)

500
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:40,500
I'm sorry.

501
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:41,829
It's fine.

502
00:21:44,369 --> 00:21:47,009
- Talking about it made her cry.
- Excuse me.

503
00:21:47,009 --> 00:21:48,009
Who are you?

504
00:21:49,539 --> 00:21:51,509
It's Leon!

505
00:21:51,509 --> 00:21:53,250
- Leon.
- It's Leon.

506
00:21:53,250 --> 00:21:55,549
- A bag instead of a plant.
- It's Leon.

507
00:21:57,950 --> 00:22:00,619
- The greatest scene for me...
- Yes?

508
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,819
is where Kim So Yeon...

509
00:22:02,289 --> 00:22:05,559
takes out a phone's SIM card
and chews it.

510
00:22:06,390 --> 00:22:10,099
(The phone contained a video
that incriminated her.)

511
00:22:13,529 --> 00:22:15,029
The script said...

512
00:22:15,029 --> 00:22:18,000
I flush the SIM card
down the toilet.

513
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:20,009
The director said, "So Yeon."

514
00:22:20,009 --> 00:22:21,839
"We prepared a SIM card
made with chewing gum."

515
