00:52:48,969 --> 00:52:52,070
So I'm really curious...

1266
00:52:52,070 --> 00:52:54,739
what I can do in the drama.

1267
00:52:54,739 --> 00:52:57,440
Right. Is there anything...

1268
00:52:57,440 --> 00:52:59,909
you expect to happen?

1269
00:52:59,909 --> 00:53:02,650
Maybe a relationship with anyone?

1270
00:53:02,650 --> 00:53:04,679
Should I look in Tae Gyu's eyes?

1271
00:53:05,050 --> 00:53:06,349
(Interested)

1272
00:53:06,920 --> 00:53:09,320
- What about me?
- But Ki Joon...

1273
00:53:09,320 --> 00:53:11,449
- She's surprised.
- We were the perfect couple for...

1274
00:53:11,449 --> 00:53:14,219
two seasons in a row.
What's happening to me?

1275
00:53:14,219 --> 00:53:16,829
Honestly, I think Yoon Hee's
sick of men.

1276
00:53:16,829 --> 00:53:20,059
- No more?
- No more. Go away.

1277
00:53:20,300 --> 00:53:21,300
(Cutting off her ties
with Ha Yoon Chul)

1278
00:53:21,300 --> 00:53:25,300
Ha Yoon Chul's nickname is
the Korean Charlie Chaplin.

1279
00:53:25,300 --> 00:53:27,869
Charlie Chaplin had
dozens of children.

1280
00:53:28,170 --> 00:53:29,940
So in the next seaon,

1281
00:53:29,940 --> 00:53:33,179
we have to focus on
how many children Ha Yoon Chul has.

1282
00:53:34,010 --> 00:53:35,449
Okay.

1283
00:53:35,550 --> 00:53:37,579
- Just kidding.
- Yes.

1284
00:53:37,579 --> 00:53:41,019
Do you want a happy ending
with Cheon Seo Jin...

1285
00:53:41,019 --> 00:53:43,690
or Oh Yoon Hee?

1286
00:53:43,690 --> 00:53:47,090
Who do you have in your heart?
Let's say it for fun.

1287
00:53:47,090 --> 00:53:48,960
- For fun?
- Of course.

1288
00:53:48,960 --> 00:53:51,599
She said she doesn't need me,
so I choose her.

1289
00:53:52,360 --> 00:53:55,500
He carried it inside himself.

1290
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:57,869
- I don't need you.
- He's hurt.

1291
00:53:57,969 --> 00:53:59,340
You take him.

1292
00:54:00,039 --> 00:54:01,869
Come to charming Kyu Jin.

1293
00:54:01,869 --> 00:54:03,469
(Kyu Jin doesn't miss his chance.)

1294
00:54:03,539 --> 00:54:05,480
Call me when you're lonely.

1295
00:54:05,579 --> 00:54:07,309
This is crazy.

1296
00:54:07,510 --> 00:54:08,710
- Logan Lee.
- Yes.

1297
00:54:08,710 --> 00:54:10,750
- In Season Three?
- Yes.

1298
00:54:10,750 --> 00:54:14,019
As you saw...

1299
00:54:14,019 --> 00:54:16,449
- Are you dead or live?
- I know.

1300
00:54:16,449 --> 00:54:21,090
If I return,
I'd probably take revenge.

1301
00:54:21,090 --> 00:54:23,530
He went after me this time.

1302
00:54:23,530 --> 00:54:25,960
So it's going to get
a little more personal.

1303
00:54:26,159 --> 00:54:28,300
That's what I expect.

1304
00:54:28,300 --> 00:54:29,969
If not,

1305
00:54:30,570 --> 00:54:32,869
I'll enjoy watching
Season Three at home.

1306
00:54:33,599 --> 00:54:35,739
You go back to being a viewer.

1307
00:54:35,739 --> 00:54:37,809
He said those things,

1308
00:54:37,809 --> 00:54:41,309
but what he desperately wants is
that he wants to live.

1309
00:54:41,309 --> 00:54:42,610
(What Logan Lee really wants
is to survive.)

1310
00:54:42,880 --> 00:54:45,349
- The last episode was a bit...
- He wishes he didn't die.

1311
00:54:45,349 --> 00:54:47,650
I hope you return
by all means necessary.

1312
00:54:47,650 --> 00:54:49,219
Yes. Thank you.

1313
00:54:49,289 --> 00:54:52,960
The production crew mentioned...

1314
00:54:52,960 --> 00:54:56,730
about Season Three...

1315
00:54:56,730 --> 00:54:58,960
that neither the actors...

1316
00:54:58,960 --> 00:55:00,860
- nor we know.
- Right.

1317
00:55:00,860 --> 00:55:02,429
Really?

1318
00:55:02,530 --> 00:55:05,969
They said...

1319
00:55:05,969 --> 00:55:07,670
- the actors are very curious...
- Yes.

1320
00:55:07,670 --> 00:55:09,610
and they'll like it too.

1321
00:55:09,610 --> 00:55:13,110
But it's not about what we expect...

1322
00:55:13,110 --> 00:55:15,010
or what the rumors say.

1323
00:55:15,010 --> 00:55:16,880
We got the script.

1324
00:55:16,880 --> 00:55:19,219
- What?
- It's shocking.

1325
00:55:19,219 --> 00:55:21,579
- This is real.
- Not even the actors know.

1326
00:55:21,579 --> 00:55:24,090
- You've never seen it before.
- We haven't received it yet.

1327
00:55:24,090 --> 00:55:25,260
I'm getting goosebumps.

1328
00:55:25,260 --> 00:55:26,920
The script is so thick.

1329
00:55:26,920 --> 00:55:29,230
- He must be really curious.
- I'm utterly shocked.

1330
00:55:29,230 --> 00:55:32,260
- I can't wait to read it.
- It's so shocking.

1331
00:55:32,260 --> 00:55:33,900
Has it been printed?

1332
00:55:33,900 --> 00:55:36,099
Only two scripts have been printed.

1333
00:55:36,099 --> 00:55:38,230
Only Writer Kim Soon Ok,

1334
00:55:38,230 --> 00:55:40,139
- Director Ju Dong Min...
- I should read that before I go.

1335
00:55:40,139 --> 00:55:42,869
and the two of us know
what it's about.

1336
00:55:42,869 --> 00:55:45,579
I can't believe it.

1337
00:55:45,710 --> 00:55:47,179
Season Three.

1338
00:55:47,179 --> 00:55:48,409
(The script won't be shared
for security.)

1339
00:55:48,409 --> 00:55:49,579
Episode One.

1340
00:55:50,550 --> 00:55:51,610
(Surprised)

1341
00:55:52,380 --> 00:55:54,019
Seriously.

1342
00:55:54,019 --> 00:55:55,420
- Why did I close my eyes?
- Take it away!

1343
00:55:55,420 --> 00:55:57,820
- Why did I close my eyes?
- Take it, So Yeon.

1344
00:55:57,820 --> 00:55:59,360
Can you read one, please?

1345
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:01,860
Should I check if Eun Seok's in it?

1346
00:56:04,130 --> 00:56:09,070
I don't quite like...

1347
00:56:09,070 --> 00:56:12,500
acting childish.

1348
00:56:12,599 --> 00:56:14,139
- But...
- You're going to act childish.

1349
00:56:14,139 --> 00:56:16,210
I'm serious.

1350
00:56:16,440 --> 00:56:18,269
(Reading the script)

1351
00:56:18,269 --> 00:56:19,909
- I'm curious.
- What does it say?

1352
00:56:21,579 --> 00:56:24,250
- Joo Dan Tae!
- Oh, I'm sorry.

1353
00:56:24,250 --> 00:56:27,250
- Joo Dan Tae!
- Seriously.

1354
00:56:27,250 --> 00:56:29,889
If you have anything sharp,
give it to me.

1355
00:56:29,889 --> 00:56:33,289
Joo Dan Tae! Seriously, Joo Dan Tae.

1356
00:56:33,889 --> 00:56:35,929
He's really annoying.

1357
00:56:36,090 --> 00:56:38,260
Look. This is what happens.

1358
00:56:38,260 --> 00:56:40,159
- This is what happens.
- I'm not curious.

1359
00:56:40,159 --> 00:56:42,929
Look what happens here.

1360
00:56:45,699 --> 00:56:47,699
- I'm curious.
- What?

1361
00:56:47,699 --> 00:56:49,369
(What's Season 3 Episode 1 about?)

1362
00:56:49,769 --> 00:56:51,239
- That's intense.
- My goodness.

1363
00:56:51,239 --> 00:56:52,880
This episode...

1364
00:56:52,880 --> 00:56:55,610
is the most shocking...

1365
00:56:55,610 --> 00:56:57,849
- first episode so far.
- Right.

1366
00:56:57,849 --> 00:57:00,849
- As an incident occurs,
- Again?

1367
00:57:00,849 --> 00:57:03,250
Season Three begins.

1368
00:57:03,250 --> 00:57:05,420
Something amazing is going to happen
in here.

1369
00:57:05,420 --> 00:57:07,460
Will Seol A come back alive?

1370
00:57:07,920 --> 00:57:09,460
That's not a statue.

1371
00:57:09,530 --> 00:57:11,590
- It wasn't a statue.
- It's been watching all along.

1372
00:57:11,590 --> 00:57:13,429
- A person in body painting?
- Yes.

1373
00:57:13,429 --> 00:57:15,170
- "Body painting".
- Is it an actor?

1374
00:57:15,170 --> 00:57:18,099
It's Seo Jang Hoon in disguise.

1375
00:57:18,940 --> 00:57:20,170
That's possible.

1376
00:57:20,170 --> 00:57:22,610
- The statue comes alive?
- If the statue moves...

1377
00:57:22,610 --> 00:57:24,369
Is there a dead body
inside the statue?

1378
00:57:24,369 --> 00:57:25,739
(Surprised)

1379
00:57:25,739 --> 00:57:29,010
- That's a reasonable doubt.
- Oh, I know.

1380
00:57:29,010 --> 00:57:31,179
Does it start
with Joo Dan Tae's death?

1381
00:57:31,179 --> 00:57:33,420
- What?
- I think it's me.

1382
00:57:33,420 --> 00:57:34,650
- What?
- What?

1383
00:57:34,650 --> 00:57:36,590
Because I killed Min Seol A.

1384
00:57:36,590 --> 00:57:38,690
- Oh, that's right.
- You read it.

1385
00:57:38,690 --> 00:57:39,960
- You're right.
- You read the script.

1386
00:57:39,960 --> 00:57:42,059
Don't act like you didn't read it.

1387
00:57:42,059 --> 00:57:43,130
No.

1388
00:57:43,130 --> 00:57:45,460
Logan Lee said no.

1389
00:57:45,460 --> 00:57:47,059
I think there's a dead body
inside it.

1390
00:57:47,059 --> 00:57:49,469
I was thinking...

1391
00:57:49,469 --> 00:57:51,030
where the dead body could be.

1392
00:57:51,800 --> 00:57:54,869
When you break it,

1393
00:57:54,869 --> 00:57:56,969
a woman lies inside just like that.

1394
00:57:56,969 --> 00:57:58,269
In that shape?

1395
00:57:58,269 --> 00:58:00,840
My goodness. In that shape?

1396
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:03,250
Let me give you a heads up.

1397
00:58:04,380 --> 00:58:07,019
Let's not air this.
Let's just share it with actors.

1398
00:58:07,019 --> 00:58:09,489
- No. We can't.
- It's okay.

1399
00:58:09,489 --> 00:58:10,849
No, we can't.

1400
00:58:10,849 --> 00:58:12,719
As the statue breaks,

1401
00:58:12,719 --> 00:58:15,860
a man who looks just like it
walks out.

1402
00:58:15,860 --> 00:58:16,860
(She got fooled.)

1403
00:58:16,860 --> 00:58:18,599
That's actually a man.

1404
00:58:18,730 --> 00:58:19,760
(She didn't get fooled.)

1405
00:58:19,760 --> 00:58:22,199
- Gosh.
- Oh, that's the secret.

1406
00:58:22,199 --> 00:58:24,469
It wasn't a woman. It was a man.

1407
00:58:24,599 --> 00:58:25,769
It's not the statue of Hera,

1408
00:58:25,769 --> 00:58:27,599
- but Hercules.
- Is it the statue of Zeus?

1409
00:58:28,170 --> 00:58:30,739
- "Hercules".
- Is that true?

1410
00:58:30,739 --> 00:58:31,840
- It says in here.
- What a shocking twist.

1411
00:58:31,840 --> 00:58:34,480
As the statue of Hera breaks,
Hercules comes out.

1412
00:58:36,349 --> 00:58:39,719
My goodness. I can't wait to say it.

1413
00:58:39,949 --> 00:58:42,289
The Penthouse 3...

1414
00:58:42,289 --> 00:58:44,949
will begin in early June.

1415
00:58:45,119 --> 00:58:47,090
When it starts to get hot,

1416
00:58:47,090 --> 00:58:50,360
watch The Penthouse 3
and cool things off.

1417
00:58:50,360 --> 00:58:54,059
Do we get to meet again
for The Penthouse 3 Special?

1418
00:58:54,429 --> 00:58:57,369
See you in The Penthouse 3.

1419
00:58:57,369 --> 00:59:01,039
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1420
00:59:01,039 --> 00:59:03,639
I don't think I have a chance
to say this...

1421
00:59:03,639 --> 00:59:05,940
unless I say it now.

1422
00:59:05,940 --> 00:59:09,179
The Penthouse production crew
worked really hard.

1423
00:59:09,179 --> 00:59:11,349
Including Director Ju
and Writer Kim,

1424
00:59:11,349 --> 00:59:13,280
directing team, filming team,
lighting team,

1425
00:59:13,280 --> 00:59:15,019
audio team,
props team and arts team.

1426
00:59:15,019 --> 00:59:17,719
As the shoot continued
for over a year,

1427
00:59:17,719 --> 00:59:20,789
all actors really pulled it off.

1428
00:59:20,789 --> 00:59:23,489
I hope the viewers know that.

1429
00:59:23,489 --> 00:59:25,159
And please give us
a lot of compliments.

1430
00:59:25,159 --> 00:59:26,929
I thought...

1431
00:59:26,929 --> 00:59:29,730
it'd make my day if I could say it.

1432
00:59:29,730 --> 00:59:31,769
You won't edit it out, will you?
Please air it.

1433
00:59:31,769 --> 00:59:35,369
- Please air it. Promise.
- Thank you.

1434
00:59:35,840 --> 00:59:37,769
(Please look forward to
The Penthouse 3.)

